message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The patient's symptoms and pelvic ultrasonography findings suggest ovarian cancer, specifically mucinous ovarian cancer. Gastric wall thickening is a common metastatic site for mucinous ovarian cancer, while the other options are not associated with this condition. Further evaluation is likely to include imaging, tumor marker testing, and staging to determine the extent and spread of the cancer.
